released     = {{Start date|2020|1|10|mf=yes}}\n| recorded     = <!-- Please source recording dates/years -->\n| studio       = \n| genre        =\n* [[Heavy metal music|Heavy metal]]\n* [[Pop music|pop]] \n* [[electropop]]\n* {{nowrap|[[nu metal]]}}\n* [[dream pop]]\n* [[Industrial music|industrial]]\n<!-- Do NOT add genres without a source to support them. These genres are sourced in the composition section. -->\n| label        = {{hlist|[[Sumerian Records|Sumerian]]|[[Warner Music Group|Warner]]}}\n| length       = 35:08\n| producer     =\n* Chris Greatti\n* Zakk Cervini\n| prev_title   = I C U: Music to Read To\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = Music to Scream To\n| next_year    = 2020\n| misc         = {{Extra chronology\n | artist       = [[Poppy (entertainer)|Poppy]] studio album\n | type         = studio\n | prev_title   = [[Am I a Girl?]]\n | prev_year    = 2018\n | title        = I Disagree\n | year         = 2020\n | next_title   = \n | next_year    = \n}}\n{{Singles\n | name        = I Disagree\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Concrete\n | single1date = August 22, 2019\n | single2     = I Disagree\n | single2date = October 4, 2019\n | single3     = [[Bloodmoney]]\n | single3date = November 6, 2019\n | single4     = Fill the Crown\n | single4date = December 11, 2019\n | single5     = Anything Like Me\n | single5date = January 10, 2020<ref name=\"Facebook\">{{cite web |author=Poppy |title=Anything Like Me Friday |url=https://www.facebook.com/Poppy/videos/508754863076814/ |via=Facebook |accessdate=January 7, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''I Disagree''''' is the third studio album by American singer and [[YouTuber|YouTube personality]] [[Poppy (entertainer)|Poppy]]. It was released on January 10, 2020, via [[Sumerian Records]].<ref name=\"release\"/> It is her first release on Sumerian Records following her departure from [[Mad Decent]] in 2019. It is also her final collaborative project with [[Titanic Sinclair]] before the end of their creative partnership in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|last=Childers |first=Chad |title=Poppy Splits With Creative Partner Titanic Sinclair|url=https://loudwire.com/poppy-splits-creative-partner-titanic-sinclair/|accessdate=December 29, 2019 |work=[[Loudwire]] |date=December 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\n''I Disagree'' debuted at number 130 on the [[Billboard 200]] in the week of January 25, 2020, becoming Poppy's first entry on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-200/2020-01-25|title=Billboard 200 (Week of January 25, 2020)|date=January 25, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Background and release==\nPoppy began work on ''I Disagree'' shortly after the release of ''[[Am I a Girl?]]'', calling the album \"post-genre\" and \"heavy\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Trefor |first=Cai |title= Poppy talks new ambient release, being a religious leader + embracing heavy metal |url=https://www.gigwise.com/features/3304522/poppy-interview-new-coming-book-release-and-companion-album|accessdate=December 11, 2019 |work=[[Gigwise]] |date=January 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n\"Concrete\" was released as the lead single from the album on August 22, 2019. It was released alongside a music video. The release of \"Concrete\" came shortly after an announcement of Poppy signing with Sumerian Records.<ref name=\"concrete\">{{cite news |last=Shoemaker |first=Whitney |title=Poppy debuts new track \"Concrete\", signs with Sumerian Records |url=https://www.altpress.com/news/poppy-concrete-sumerian-records/|accessdate=December 11, 2019 |work=[[Alternative Press (magazine)|Alternative Press]] |date=August 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe album's cover, title and release date were revealed on September 30, 2019 via Poppy's social media accounts. The album art was done by Jesse Draxler.<ref name=\"release\">{{Cite tweet |user=poppy |number=1178701511011926017 |date = September 30, 2019 |title= My album I DISAGREE comes out January 10 (1/10) on @sumerianrecords Art by @jessedraxler + #IDisagree single + pre order + pre save available Friday }}</ref>\n\n\"I Disagree\" was released as the second single from the album on October 4, 2019, alongside a music video.<ref name=\"disagree\">{{cite news |last=Divita |first=Joe |title= Poppy\u2019s Pop Metal Rebirth Continues on New Song 'I Disagree'|url= https://loudwire.com/poppy-i-disagree-lyrics-music-video/|accessdate=December 11, 2019 |work=[[Loudwire]] |date=October 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n\"[[Bloodmoney]]\" was released as the third single from the album on November 6, 2019, along with the announcement of a 2020 US tour in support of ''I Disagree'' and a music video.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Robinson |first1=Dominiq |title= Poppy announces 2020 dates for I Disagree US tour|url= https://www.axs.com/poppy-announces-2020-dates-for-i-disagree-us-tour-138582|accessdate=December 11, 2019 |work=[[AXS (company)|AXS]] |date=November 6, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"bloodmoney\">{{cite news |last=Shoemaker |first=Whitney |title= Poppy kicks ass and takes names in new \"BLOODMONEY\" video |url= https://www.altpress.com/news/poppy-bloodmoney-video/|accessdate=December 11, 2019 |work=[[Alternative Press (magazine)|Altpress]] |date=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe tracklist of ''I Disagree'' was revealed via Poppy's social media on November 26, 2019.<ref>{{Citation |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B5VqOILgyOZ/ |title= Poppy (@impoppy) on Instagram |website=[[Instagram]] |access-date=November 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n\"Fill the Crown\" was released as the fourth single from the album on December 11, 2019, alongside a music video.<ref name=\"crown\">{{cite news |last1=Schaffner |first1=Lauryn |title= Poppy Doesn't Believe in Genres, Shares New Song 'Fill the Crown' \u2014 Exclusive Interview|url=https://loudwire.com/poppy-interview-new-song-fill-the-crown/|accessdate=December 11, 2019 |work=[[Loudwire]] |date=December 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n\"Anything Like Me\" was released as the album's fifth single on the same day as the album - January 10, 2020,<ref name=\"Facebook\"/> with the music video directed by Jesse Draxler and Poppy.\n\nA video for \"Sit / Stay\" was released on March 20, 2020.\n\n==Composition==\n''I Disagree'' has been described as a [[Heavy metal music|heavy metal]],<ref name=\"Clash\">{{cite web |last=Gray |first=Josh |title=Poppy \u2013 I Disagree |url=https://www.clashmusic.com/reviews/poppy-i-disagree |accessdate=January 10, 2020 |work=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]] |date=January 10, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"PopMatters\"/><ref name=\"Slant Magazine\"/> [[Pop music|pop]],<ref name=\"The Line of Best Fit\">{{cite web |last=Horton|first=Ross|title=Poppy\u2019s I Disagree is a bewildering sugar rush\n|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/reviews/albums/poppy-i-disagree-album-review|accessdate=January 10, 2020 |work=[[The Line of Best Fit]] |date=January 10, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"PopMatters\"/> [[pop-metal]],<ref name=\"AllMusic\"/> [[electropop]],<ref name=\"The Guardian\"/> [[industrial rock]],<ref name=\"Slant Magazine\"/> [[nu metal]],<ref name=\"The Guardian\"/> [[hard rock]],<ref name=\"riff\">{{cite web |last=DeWald|first=Mike|title=Album Review: Poppy burns down convention on expansive \u2018I Disagree\u2019|url=https://riffmagazine.com/album-reviews/poppy-i-disagree/|accessdate=January 10, 2020 |work=Riff Magazine|date=January 7, 2020}}</ref> and [[Industrial music|industrial]]<ref name=\"riff\"/> record, which uses elements of [[art rock]], [[dubstep]], [[progressive metal]], [[thrash metal]], [[Rock music|rock]], [[dream pop]], [[Alternative pop|alt-pop]], acoustic pop, and [[J-pop]].<ref name=\"The Line of Best Fit\"/><ref name=\"AllMusic\"/> Speaking in an interview with ''[[Kerrang!]]'', Poppy said \"I've never said my music is metal, but I do listen to that music.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/poppy-ive-never-said-my-music-is-metal/|title=Poppy: \u201cI\u2019ve Never Said My Music Is Metal\u2026 We\u2019re Turning A New Page\u201d|work=Kerrang!|accessdate=January 14, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200111101719/https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/poppy-ive-never-said-my-music-is-metal/|archive-date=January 11, 2020|url-status=}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Album reviews\n| ADM = 6.6/10<ref name=\"ADM\">{{cite web |title=I Disagree by Poppy reviews |url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/10194/Poppy-I-Disagree.aspx|accessdate=February 2, 2020 |publisher=[[AnyDecentMusic?]]}}</ref>\n| MC = 72/100<ref name=\"MC1\">{{cite web |title=I Disagree by Poppy Reviews and Tracks |url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/i-disagree/poppy |accessdate=February 2, 2020 |publisher=[[Metacritic]]}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"AllMusic\">{{cite web |last=Yeung |first=Neil Z. |title=I Disagree \u2013 Poppy |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/i-disagree-mw0003324404 |accessdate=January 9, 2020 |publisher=[[AllMusic]]}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n| rev2score = 5/10<ref name=\"Exclaim!\">{{cite web |last=Feibel |first=Adam |title=Poppy: I Disagree |url=https://exclaim.ca/music/article/poppy-i_disagree |accessdate=January 10, 2020 |work=[[Exclaim!]] |date=January 8, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Gigwise]]''\n| rev3score = {{Rating|9|10}}<ref name=\"Gigwise\">{{cite web |last=Padin |first=Malvika |title=Album Review: Poppy - I Disagree |url=https://www.gigwise.com/reviews/3368786/album-review-poppy-i-disagree |accessdate=January 15, 2020 |work=[[Gigwise]] |date=January 9, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev4score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"The Guardian\">{{cite web |last=Cliff |first=Aimee |title=Poppy: I Disagree review \u2013 online pop-bot embraces IRL nu-metal |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/jan/10/poppy-i-disagree-review |accessdate=January 10, 2020 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=January 10, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[MusicOMH]]''\n| rev5score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"musicOMH\">{{cite web|last=Wylde|first=Nicoletta|title=Poppy \u2013 I Disagree|url=https://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/poppy-i-disagree|accessdate=January 15, 2020|work=[[musicOMH]]|date=January 14, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[NME]]''\n| rev6score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web |last=Shutler |first=Ali |title=Poppy \u2013 'I Disagree' review: a very modern pop star sheds her satirical skin |url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/poppy-i-disagree-review-a-very-modern-pop-star-sheds-her-satirical-skin-2594710 |accessdate=January 9, 2020 |work=[[NME]] |date=January 9, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[The Observer]]''\n| rev7score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"The Observer\">{{cite web |last=Joshi |first=Tara |title=Poppy: I Disagree review \u2013 candyfloss pop with a dark heart |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/jan/12/poppy-i-disagree-review |accessdate=January 12, 2020 |work=[[The Observer]] |date=January 15, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev8score = 6.5/10<ref name=\"Pitchfork\">{{cite web |last=Joyce |first=Colin |title=Poppy: I Disagree |url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/poppy-i-disagree/ |accessdate=January 15, 2020 |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date=January 15, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[PopMatters]]''\n| rev9score = 7/10<ref name=\"PopMatters\">{{cite web |last=Woronzoff |first=Elisabeth |title=Poppy Expands Her Musicality and Challenges Genre Conventions on 'I Disagree' |url=https://www.popmatters.com/poppy-i-disagree-review-2644653003.html |accessdate=January 10, 2020 |work=[[PopMatters]] |date=January 9, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[Slant Magazine]]''\n| rev10score = {{rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=\"Slant Magazine\">{{cite web |last=Cinquemani |first=Sal |title=Review: Poppy\u2019s I Disagree Obliterates the Niceties of Genre Convention |url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review-poppy-i-disagree-obliterates-the-niceties-of-genre-convention/ |accessdate=January 11, 2020 |work=[[Slant Magazine]] |date=January 11, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''I Disagree'' received generally positive reviews from critics. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a normalized rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, the album has an average score of 72 out of 100, which indicates \"Generally favorable reviews\" based on 15 reviews.<ref name=\"MC1\"/>\n\nAli Shutler of ''[[NME]]'' praised ''I Disagree'' as \"her most accomplished record, full of daring theatre and snarling forward motion\".<ref name=\"NME\"/> [[AllMusic]] writer Neil Z. Yeung also gave the album a positive rating, writing that \"As both a symbolic avatar for her life changes and a strong empowerment statement, ''I Disagree'' celebrates Poppy's rebirth as a pop-metal alchemist and unabashed rule-breaker.\"<ref name=\"AllMusic\"/> Josh Gray of ''[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]'' opined that the album would \"seriously divide opinions across the spectrum, from the trvest of metal [to the] sugariest of pop [[Stan (fan)|stans]]\", while nonetheless concluding that \"Poppy remains a daring and divisive artist making daring and divisive art, and ''I Disagree'' is the perfect shot of adrenaline to kick start a new decade with.\"<ref name=\"Clash\"/>\n\nMalvika Padin of ''[[Gigwise]]'' called the album \"A true masterpiece in almost every way imaginable...\" and \"...the perfect album to start 2020 with.\"<ref name=\"Gigwise\"/> While talking positively about the album, Nicoletta Wylde of ''[[musicOMH]]'' stated, \"with ''I Disagree'', Poppy releases her version of ''[[Lemonade (Beyonc\u00e9 album)|Lemonade]]''; both channelling the pain of her recent controversy, sticking two fingers up to the past and translating her performance art into music.\"<ref name=\"musicOMH\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]] and [[Spotify]]. Track lengths adapted from [[Qobuz]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Credits / Concrete / Poppy - TIDAL |url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/115034492/credits |website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]] |accessdate=December 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Credits / I Disagree / Poppy 